    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the CFD hemolysis predictions for regulatory submission on the basis that (a) all 5 operating points show nIH predictions within expanded uncertainty bands of experimental measurements, (b) the 8.3% mean absolute error is below the pre-specified 10% acceptance threshold, and (c) the v3.2 turbulence recalibration was assessed via internal memo to be not material to hemolysis scalar outputs. The primary experimental dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-17) predates the model revision (2025-11-10) by 24 days; the team concluded this gap does not warrant re-collection of experimental data. Remaining credibility factor gaps are acknowledged as limitations to be addressed in the next model revision cycle.",
